eem to put the focus on melee, but instead I think it dulls their impact severely.  If I can't finish a fight quickly, almost every foe I can face on the field of battle can simply turn to run and have an excellent chance to survive.  All of my combat moves require endurance on my part, so there is very little chance I'll have any endurance for a prolonged chase.  Even /stuck on an opponent, I have to sprint to have a chance to hit him during the chase, which chews up even more endurance.  Couple that with people being able to stealth while in plain sight (bugs the hell out of me), and the speed songs that so many enemy classes have, and longer fights just amount to even less chance I'll score any RP's, or be able to deal with a stealth or range class of any kind.  Not sour grapes, I know melee has its place, but disappointing and frustrating to say the least.<br><br><br>Range<br>Nothing really changes here except I have to look for foes a little closer to death to fire on.  Rangers and most stealthers are smoked in direct combat anyway, so you'll just see a little more care on our part when soloing or grouping in RvR.  Probably a lot more impact on those single shot snipes, but thats pretty much always some cheesy high 40's player sniping greens and greys anyway, and they SHOULD have a harder time of it.  Nothing is more discouraging than making the 20 minute run to Emain only to have some jerk of a kid smoke you with one shot (I use at least three with my ranger.. heh).<br><br>If anything, this change will have more people leaving the tank classes than joining them in my opinion.  If anything, give us MORE damage in close combat and less to the ranged classes.  Just my 2cp<br><br>Moradis Emberheart<br>30th level Celtic Bluntmaster<br>Malrik<br>41st level Lurikeen Ranger <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub49.ezboard.com/